text: Karin Housley (born January 20, 1964) is an American politician. She is a Republican member of the Minnesota Senate. She represents District 39 since January 8, 2013. In December 2017, Housley announced she would run for the United States Senate seat left empty by Al Franken. In August 2018, she won the Republican nomination for the Senate race. However, she lost to incumbent Tina Smith. ==References== Category:1964 births Category:Living people Category:Politicians from Minnesota Category:State legislators of the United States Category:Republican Party (United States) politicians
